content:
The `RootLayout` component in `app/layout.tsx` serves as the main structural foundation for the entire DocMed application. It sets up the global HTML structure, integrates essential third-party providers, and applies global styling and font configurations.

**Purpose:**

*   Establishes the base HTML document structure (`<html>`, `<body>`).
*   Configures global CSS variables and base styling.
*   Initializes the Clerk authentication provider for user management.
*   Applies global fonts (Geist Sans and Geist Mono) for consistent typography across the application.
*   Defines the application's metadata (title and description), which is crucial for SEO and browser tab display.

**Key Features & Exports:**

*   **`metadata` Object:** Exports an object containing metadata for the application. This includes the `title` and `description` used by Next.js for SEO and browser tab rendering.
*   **`RootLayout` Component:** The default export, a React functional component that takes `children` as a prop. This component wraps all pages and other application components, ensuring a consistent layout and context.
    *   **Props:**
        *   `children`: `React.ReactNode` - Represents the content of the current page or component being rendered within the layout.

**Integrations:**

*   **`next/font/google`:** Imports and configures the Geist Sans and Geist Mono fonts, applying them as CSS variables (`--font-geist-sans`, `--font-geist-mono`).
*   **`@clerk/nextjs`:** Wraps the entire application in `<ClerkProvider>`, enabling Clerk's authentication and user management features.

**Usage:**

The `RootLayout` component is automatically used by Next.js to wrap every page in the application. Developers do not need to explicitly import or use it; it functions as the entry point for the entire application's UI.

```tsx
// app/layout.tsx
import type { Metadata } from "next";
import { Geist, Geist_Mono } from "next/font/google";
import { ClerkProvider } from "@clerk/nextjs";
import "./globals.css";

const geistSans = Geist({
  variable: "--font-geist-sans",
  subsets: ["latin"],
});

const geistMono = Geist_Mono({
  variable: "--font-geist-mono",
  subsets: ["latin"],
});

export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: "DocMed — Self-Healing Documentation",
  description:
    "AI-powered documentation that monitors your codebase and heals itself when code changes. End doc rot forever.",
};

export default function RootLayout({
  children,
}: Readonly<{
  children: React.ReactNode;
}>) {
  return (
    <ClerkProvider>
      <html
        lang="en"
        className={`${geistSans.variable} ${geistMono.variable} h-full antialiased dark`}
      >
        <body className="min-h-full flex flex-col">{children}</body>
      </html>
    </ClerkProvider>
  );
}
```
